physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Ms H was alert and oriented, tall, thin, symmetrically developed, with no evidence for neurocutaneous disorders. Sense of smell was depressed in the right nostril. Normal pupils, visual fields, and lower cranial nerves. More coordinated with left arm despite being right-handed. Negative Romberg. Decreased right arm swing when walking, mild difficulty with right-hand rapid alternating movements, and posturing of the right hand when distracted. Detailed sensory examination was normal, as were reflexes.
